FuncDef: The display nqa upload file-info command displays information about files that a device is uploading and has attempted to upload onto a server.
Examples: The total number of upload file records is : 2
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
After the NQA file upload function is enabled, an NQA test can be started. Test result files can then be automatically uploaded on to a server. To view information about uploaded files, including files that have been uploaded and are being uploaded onto a server, run the display nqa upload file-info command. Information about the latest 500 files can be displayed.
